---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Services"
  description="Tutelare advisory engagements: oversight assessment, operating model design, and standing advisory for engineering leadership."
>
  <h1
    class="font-semibold leading-tight mb-6"
    style="font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 2.75rem)"
  >
    Services
  </h1>

  <p class="text-lg" style="color: var(--color-ink-muted)">
    <em>This page is a placeholder. Final services copy to follow.</em>
  </p>

  <section class="mt-10">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2" style="font-family: var(--font-serif)">
      Oversight Assessment
    </h2>
    <p class="text-sm mb-3" style="color: var(--color-ink-muted)">2–4 weeks</p>
    <p>
      Reviews current code-review practices, AI tool adoption, and risk concentration.
      Output: written assessment plus recommended changes prioritized by risk reduction.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-8">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2" style="font-family: var(--font-serif)">
      Operating Model Design
    </h2>
    <p class="text-sm mb-3" style="color: var(--color-ink-muted)">6–10 weeks</p>
    <p>
      Designs the risk-tiering rubric, the adversarial-AI review process, the
      human-attention routing rules, and the accountability structure. Output:
      implementation-ready operating model with a rollout plan.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-8">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2" style="font-family: var(--font-serif)">
      Standing Advisory
    </h2>
    <p class="text-sm mb-3" style="color: var(--color-ink-muted)">Monthly retainer</p>
    <p>
      Ongoing access for engineering leadership facing specific decisions. Quarterly review
      of practices against emerging research findings. Output: continuous course correction.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 text-sm" style="color: var(--color-ink-muted)">
    <p>
      Tutelare works with organizations that have made the decision to scale AI-assisted
      development. Not for organizations still debating adoption. Pricing discussed
      one-on-one.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
